<item>
            <title>[FLINK-3863] Yarn Cluster shutdown may fail if leader changed recently</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-3863</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;ApplicationClient&lt;/tt&gt; sets &lt;tt&gt;yarnJobManager&lt;/tt&gt; to &lt;tt&gt;None&lt;/tt&gt; until it has connected to a newly elected JobManager. A shutdown message to the application master is discarded while the ApplicationClient tries to reconnect. The ApplicationClient should retry to shutdown the cluster when it is connected to the new leader. It may also time out (which currently is always the case).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
